  "texts": [
    "We refer the reader to Rousseau (2016) and Ghosal and Van der Vaart (2017) on this topic, see also Banerjee et al. (2021b) on high-dimensional models specifically.",
    "Usually, such results require two assumptions:",
    "• a technical condition, the existence of tests to discriminate between members of the model {P θ, θ ∈ Θ},",
    "• and the prior mass condition, which states that enough mass is given by the prior to a neighborhood of θ *.",
    "In other words, π({θ: d(θ, θ *) ≤ r}) does not converge too fast to 0 when r → 0, for some distance or risk measure d. For example, we can assume that there is a sequence r n → 0 when n → ∞ such that π({θ: d(θ, θ *) ≤ r n }) ≥ e -nrn."
  ],
